item.title: What can it be?
item.dc:creator: @RXVL RXVL
item.description:
@RXVL wrote:

[quote=“zammyking111, post:4, topic:150757”][quote author=Ryan_ link=topic=206350.msg1815361#msg1815361 date=1192072907]
Heres your problem

Manufacturer: Compaq

[/quote]

I agree with you xD i heard compaq aint a good company
When i get a job im making a computer from scratch any ideas
Ps: has to be good for gaming and fast
And also dont worry about graphic card i got my eye on a dual graphic card that equals to 1gb has its own fan attached to it :)[/quote]

Get a new computer before you get a graphic card, and read up on custom computers, because by judging what you just posted, you don’t know shit about computers.

Get CCleaner and NOD32 + Crack from demonoid and completely clean out your PC, the best method IMO is just to completely wipe Windows and reinstall it (or if you want to be cool, get a Linux distro).

EDIT: I just looked at your graphics card specs, and it’s fine. Look into a http://www.cyberpowerpc.com/ computer, they make some pretty sick rigs, and start subscribing to CPU magazine and PC Gamer, you’ll learn lots.
